WEBVTT

00:00.201 --> 00:01.720
<i>Previously on "Switched at Birth"... </i>

00:01.902 --> 00:03.536
<i>She's known since 1998 that
the girls were switched?</i>

00:03.570 --> 00:05.505
I found out when Daphne was three.

00:05.539 --> 00:09.342
You kept my daughter from me for 13 years!

00:12.128 --> 00:13.962
I will never forgive you for that.

00:13.997 --> 00:15.197
And the more that I know you,

00:15.231 --> 00:19.101
the more I realize I was
right to keep it a secret.

00:19.135 --> 00:20.803
You would have taken
both girls away from me.

00:20.837 --> 00:22.938
You are damn right I would have.

00:26.676 --> 00:27.943
John!

00:34.684 --> 00:35.751
John?

00:38.254 --> 00:39.555
John? Can you hear me?

00:39.589 --> 00:42.274
<i>Operator: 9-1-1.
What's your emergency?</i>

00:42.325 --> 00:44.426
It's my neighbor. I can't get a pulse.

00:44.461 --> 00:46.128
<i>Operator: Start compressions.</i>

00:46.146 --> 00:47.396
Okay.

00:47.430 --> 00:49.264
One, two, three, four,

00:49.299 --> 00:51.133
five, six, seven, eight,

00:51.167 --> 00:54.169
<i>nine, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14... </i>

00:57.173 --> 00:58.807
(Sputtering)

00:58.842 --> 00:59.942
Bam!

00:59.976 --> 01:01.943
(Chuckles)

01:01.961 --> 01:03.545
Come here, you.

01:03.563 --> 01:05.513
Oh, sweaty!

01:05.483 --> 01:06.550
Yeah, and I beat my best time.

01:06.584 --> 01:07.551
How about that?

01:07.585 --> 01:09.319
Those rookies better watch their backs.

01:09.354 --> 01:10.587
- Yeah, they'd better.
- There you go.

01:10.622 --> 01:12.589
Toby, Bay! Time for breakfast.

01:12.624 --> 01:14.224
Breakfast.

01:14.259 --> 01:16.427
<i>Kathryn: Oh now, don't run. Don't run.</i>

01:16.461 --> 01:19.179
Hey, curly. How are you this morning?

01:19.230 --> 01:21.231
Mmm!

01:21.249 --> 01:23.200
Ready for breakfast?

01:23.234 --> 01:25.035
All right. I hope everybody's hungry.

01:26.137 --> 01:27.404
Here you go, my little skunkerroo.

01:27.439 --> 01:29.239
Your purple one. And here you go,

01:29.274 --> 01:31.175
my little squirrel. All righty.

01:31.209 --> 01:32.910
<i>- (Phone ringing)
- Just muffins?</i>

01:32.944 --> 01:34.778
I want the purple one.

01:34.813 --> 01:37.848
<i>Kathryn: The purple one is hers, honey.</i>

01:37.882 --> 01:39.049
- I want it.
- But, honey.

01:39.084 --> 01:40.851
I don't understand.

01:40.885 --> 01:42.586
<i>- I want it.
- You can have the purple one tomorrow.</i>

01:42.620 --> 01:43.787
- I want it!
- Quiet.

01:44.823 --> 01:45.889
What is it?

01:49.327 --> 01:51.295
Is something wrong?

01:53.000 --> 01:59.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:03.875 --> 02:07.044
<i>The other mother discovered the little
girl wasn't hers about six weeks ago.</i>

02:07.078 --> 02:09.713
She alerted the hospital,
they investigated to find out

02:09.747 --> 02:11.014
who the other baby might be, and... 

02:11.049 --> 02:12.616
It's our Bay.

02:13.618 --> 02:14.651
How'd she find out?

02:14.686 --> 02:16.820
The little girl got sick with meningitis.

02:16.855 --> 02:19.456
- She okay?
- She's healthy,

02:19.491 --> 02:21.258
but as a result of the infection,

02:21.292 --> 02:22.259
she went deaf.

02:22.293 --> 02:24.161
- (Sighs)
- Oh, God.

02:24.195 --> 02:27.264
What do we do?

02:27.298 --> 02:29.066
- We fix it.
- How?

02:29.100 --> 02:30.200
I don't know. But we will.

02:32.036 --> 02:33.937
<i>John: So what happens now?</i>

02:33.972 --> 02:35.305
<i>Kathryn: Do we meet the other parents?</i>

02:35.340 --> 02:37.074
I believe it's just the mother,

02:37.108 --> 02:38.275
Regina Vasquez.

02:38.309 --> 02:39.910
We're still trying to
find out about the father.

02:39.944 --> 02:41.712
What exactly do we know about this woman?

02:44.816 --> 02:46.783
She has two drunk driving arrests.

02:46.818 --> 02:47.526
What?

02:47.527 --> 02:49.630
Including one when Daphne
was in the car with her.

02:49.654 --> 02:50.787
Are you kidding me?!

02:50.822 --> 02:52.706
Oh my... this is unbelievable.

02:54.592 --> 02:55.559
How do we get our daughter back?

02:55.593 --> 02:57.327
We can't lose our Bay.

02:57.362 --> 02:58.495
We can't lose her.

02:58.530 --> 03:00.164
Of course not.

03:00.198 --> 03:02.099
Okay, you know what?

03:02.133 --> 03:04.101
We want custody of both girls.

03:06.354 --> 03:09.406
<i>Amanda: And on July 28, you were
arrested for driving while intoxicated.</i>

03:09.424 --> 03:11.308
Daphne needed stitches.

03:11.342 --> 03:13.010
She fell on the front steps,

03:13.044 --> 03:14.011
and I had to get her to the free clinic.

03:14.045 --> 03:15.179
<i>They closed at 7:00.</i>

03:15.213 --> 03:16.880
I had to get her there in time.

03:16.915 --> 03:18.949
Maybe if you'd been
supervising your daughter

03:18.983 --> 03:20.651
<i>instead of drinking, she
wouldn't have been injured.</i>

03:20.685 --> 03:22.653
- Objection.
- Overruled.

03:22.687 --> 03:25.522
I was a tenth of a point over the limit.

03:25.557 --> 03:27.457
Don't you think that
with a child in the car,

03:27.492 --> 03:29.326
any amount of alcohol is over the limit?

03:29.360 --> 03:31.461
- Of course. But... 
- How many times have you driven your daughter

03:31.496 --> 03:32.462
when you thought you were sober?

03:32.497 --> 03:33.630
It was an emergency.

03:33.665 --> 03:35.299
Your Honor, my client is... 

03:35.333 --> 03:36.466
Objection sustained.

03:42.140 --> 03:43.874
Do you know the current whereabouts

03:43.908 --> 03:45.075
of Bay's biological father?

03:45.109 --> 03:47.110
I believe he's somewhere in Italy.

03:47.145 --> 03:50.847
Angelo left when the DNA test
proved that Daphne wasn't his.

03:50.882 --> 03:52.649
He thought I had cheated on him.

03:52.684 --> 03:54.518
So you're raising Daphne by yourself?

03:54.552 --> 03:56.620
Yes.

03:56.654 --> 03:57.821
But my mother is in Puerto Rico,

03:57.855 --> 03:59.489
and I'm sure she's willing to move here.

03:59.524 --> 04:00.691
Aren't the two of you estranged?

04:03.294 --> 04:04.261
Well... 

04:04.295 --> 04:06.163
we haven't spoken in awhile, but... 

04:06.197 --> 04:08.265
And isn't that because
you resisted her attempts

04:08.299 --> 04:09.433
to help you get sober?

04:09.467 --> 04:10.500
Objection.

04:10.535 --> 04:12.936
No, that's... 

04:12.971 --> 04:14.371
that's all right.

04:14.405 --> 04:16.039
No further questions.

04:20.945 --> 04:22.913
<i>(Gavel bangs)</i>

04:24.716 --> 04:26.583
It is the opinion of this court

04:26.618 --> 04:28.685
that it would cause
undue harm to Bay Kennish

04:28.720 --> 04:31.622
if she were removed from
the only home she has known

04:31.656 --> 04:33.390
and then placed in an environment

04:33.424 --> 04:34.591
that is unstable at best.

04:34.626 --> 04:37.728
<i>Therefore, custody will
remain with the Kennishes.</i>

04:39.597 --> 04:42.266
<i>As to the matter of Daphne Vasquez,</i>

04:42.300 --> 04:45.202
the court recognizes that
Regina Vasquez has raised her

04:45.236 --> 04:47.104
for the past three years.

04:47.138 --> 04:49.306
But it cannot ignore her
substance abuse problem

04:49.340 --> 04:52.109
and disregard for the child's safety.

04:52.143 --> 04:55.012
I'm granting custody of
Daphne to the Kennishes.

04:55.046 --> 04:57.614
<i>Now I am willing to revisit the issues</i>

04:57.649 --> 05:00.684
<i>of custody and visitation of Bay and Daphne</i>

05:00.718 --> 05:03.487
<i>if and when Miss Vasquez can demonstrate</i>

05:03.521 --> 05:05.589
that she is clean and sober.

05:07.525 --> 05:09.693
Please, she's already lost
her hearing and her father.

05:09.727 --> 05:11.561
You can't take me away too.

05:11.596 --> 05:13.330
I am all she has.

05:13.364 --> 05:15.599
Please, don't do this to her.

05:15.633 --> 05:17.517
Kathryn, you're a mother.

05:17.552 --> 05:20.020
You understand, please.

05:20.071 --> 05:23.273
You wouldn't even know about
her if I hadn't said anything.

05:23.308 --> 05:25.208
Please.

05:25.243 --> 05:28.178
(Sobs) Please, don't!

05:36.988 --> 05:38.822
<i>The best thing you can do right now</i>

05:38.856 --> 05:40.957
<i>is get treatment and get sober.</i>

05:40.991 --> 05:44.461
It's the only way you're
gonna be part of her life.

05:44.495 --> 05:45.829
The other little girl too.

05:49.367 --> 05:51.301
She doesn't even
understand what's happening.

05:51.336 --> 05:53.303
She's confused.

05:53.338 --> 05:54.304
I mean, can't you see that?

05:55.473 --> 05:57.040
I'm sorry.

05:57.075 --> 05:59.009
I really do have to take her now.

06:02.413 --> 06:04.247
Okay.

06:04.265 --> 06:06.917
Can you look at me?

06:08.019 --> 06:10.754
I love you.

06:10.788 --> 06:13.156
I really do.

06:13.191 --> 06:16.059
I will always love you.

06:16.094 --> 06:18.562
And I promise... 

06:18.596 --> 06:20.831
I will come for you real soon, okay?

06:20.865 --> 06:22.766
Okay. Take your doggy.

06:22.800 --> 06:23.900
Go on.

06:31.309 --> 06:33.210
<i>Daphne: Where's mama?</i>

06:33.244 --> 06:34.511
<i>Where did mommy go?</i>

06:37.482 --> 06:40.083
(Sobbing)

06:48.993 --> 06:50.227
<i>Kathryn: Hi, sweetheart.</i>

06:50.261 --> 06:51.895
Come on in, sweetie.

06:54.866 --> 06:55.966
There you go.

06:56.000 --> 06:57.601
Hey.

06:57.635 --> 06:58.735
Hello, honey.

07:00.972 --> 07:04.674
(Inaudible)

07:13.284 --> 07:16.219
I want mommy.

07:17.555 --> 07:19.289
I want mama.

07:21.125 --> 07:22.409
Honey, come on over here.

07:22.460 --> 07:23.960
Come on over here, guys.

07:23.995 --> 07:25.979
I want you to meet your new sister.

07:26.013 --> 07:28.265
This is Toby.

07:31.135 --> 07:32.903
Daphne, this is Bay.

07:32.937 --> 07:33.870
Bay, Daphne.

07:42.947 --> 07:44.898
<i>(Theme music playing)</i>

07:44.899 --> 07:48.899
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

07:53.791 --> 07:55.408
Daphne?

07:55.460 --> 07:56.576
Daphne.

07:56.627 --> 07:57.861
Put your cochlear in, honey.

08:00.698 --> 08:01.765
So, do you want some bacon?

08:01.799 --> 08:03.433
What?

08:03.468 --> 08:04.534
Do you want some bacon?

08:04.569 --> 08:06.503
Does Christian Louboutin make great shoes?

08:07.538 --> 08:09.473
Look.

08:09.451 --> 08:11.485
<i>Ooh. "The Falconer's Mistress.</i>

08:11.520 --> 08:13.587
A tale of lovers and other birds of prey."

08:13.622 --> 08:15.389
If you don't like it, you better tell me

08:15.424 --> 08:17.658
because 100,000 of them
are about to go into print.

08:17.692 --> 08:19.493
Are you kidding me?

08:19.528 --> 08:20.694
Look at my hot mom.

08:20.729 --> 08:21.729
You think so?

08:21.763 --> 08:23.397
<i>Yes!</i>

08:23.432 --> 08:24.732
So, um... 

08:24.766 --> 08:27.635
Alisha Jelline's sweet sixteen

08:27.669 --> 08:29.720
<i>is Friday night.
Everybody's gonna be there.</i>

08:29.771 --> 08:34.707
And I was hoping maybe I could
get an extra hour on my curfew?

08:34.743 --> 08:37.561
It's parent chaperoned. And
I did pass my chemistry test.

08:37.611 --> 08:40.414
Whoa, if her "C-minus"
gets her an extra hour,

08:40.448 --> 08:42.750
my 98 should cover me until Sunday.

08:42.784 --> 08:44.452
Honey, are you going to the party?

08:44.486 --> 08:46.487
- What party?
- Mom, we have different friends.

08:46.521 --> 08:48.372
It could be really fun.

08:48.406 --> 08:49.824
Then you should go.

08:49.858 --> 08:52.543
And if you look like that, you'll
probably be asked out to the prom.

08:52.577 --> 08:54.361
Dad, come on.

08:54.396 --> 08:55.463
I gave you money last week.

08:55.497 --> 08:56.530
What happened to that?

08:56.565 --> 08:57.698
I have expenses.

08:57.716 --> 08:59.700
I want to take Jenna out.
I need like 100 bucks.

08:59.734 --> 09:02.403
Your back seat costs 100 bucks?

09:02.437 --> 09:03.587
Make do with that, my friend.

09:03.638 --> 09:05.372
Oh, I got to go.

09:05.390 --> 09:06.640
Oh, me too.

09:06.675 --> 09:08.375
Bye mom. Bye daddy.

09:08.393 --> 09:09.477
- Bye.
- Bye.

09:09.511 --> 09:11.545
- Have a good day.
- Later.

09:11.563 --> 09:13.380
Love you.

09:13.415 --> 09:15.516
So this is the new book jacket, huh?

09:15.550 --> 09:18.419
Yeah, I was hoping the Senate
majority leader could weigh in on it.

09:18.453 --> 09:20.387
- <i>Oh, it's... oh.
- (Cellphone ringing)</i>

09:21.590 --> 09:23.390
Oh, God. I gotta take this.

09:23.425 --> 09:24.391
All right. Bye.

09:26.428 --> 09:27.828
Okay.

09:27.863 --> 09:29.730
<i>Simone: So we all set for Friday?</i>

09:29.748 --> 09:31.565
<i>Daphne: Oh yeah. What'd
you tell your parents?</i>

09:31.583 --> 09:33.734
That we're going to a college party.

09:33.752 --> 09:35.402
The truth?

09:35.420 --> 09:36.737
So much for getting our stories straight.

09:36.755 --> 09:38.622
As long as I don't drive drunk,

09:38.673 --> 09:40.508
always carry pepper spray on me,

09:40.542 --> 09:43.577
and don't take drinks I didn't
mix myself, they trust me.

09:43.595 --> 09:46.580
Should we invite Wilke, or is that
like bringing sand to the beach?

09:46.598 --> 09:48.582
- (Clears throat)
- What?

09:48.617 --> 09:50.751
Okay, it's better I tell you.

09:50.769 --> 09:54.588
Kaylee saw Wilke hooking
up with Clover Ramberg.

09:54.606 --> 09:57.424
They're like a thing now. I'm sorry.

09:57.459 --> 09:58.592
Hey.

10:00.462 --> 10:02.596
French?

10:02.631 --> 10:04.598
You know what? Let's ditch.

10:04.633 --> 10:05.766
Get something hot to wear to the party.

10:10.772 --> 10:13.507
I was thinking if I
take three extra credits,

10:13.542 --> 10:15.743
and do summer school, I could
graduate a semester early.

10:15.777 --> 10:16.710
Why?

10:16.745 --> 10:19.146
Just get a jumpstart on college.

10:19.180 --> 10:21.248
Start all that learning
a little bit faster.

10:21.283 --> 10:23.050
Challenge the old noggin.

10:23.084 --> 10:24.985
Bay, college will come soon enough.

10:25.020 --> 10:27.121
And I bet your parents aren't
gonna want you to fly the coop

10:27.155 --> 10:29.023
six months early.

10:29.057 --> 10:29.990
You sure about that?

10:30.025 --> 10:31.292
What do you mean?

10:31.326 --> 10:34.028
Look, everyone wants to pretend

10:34.062 --> 10:36.030
that we're this happy little family.

10:36.064 --> 10:38.599
Two bio kids, one adopted.

10:38.633 --> 10:39.667
Perfectly blended.

10:39.701 --> 10:41.502
But I'm not one of them.

10:41.536 --> 10:42.836
They know it.

10:42.871 --> 10:44.605
And I know it.

10:44.639 --> 10:47.441
Honey, I've spoken to your
parents numerous times.

10:47.475 --> 10:49.243
And I've never gotten the impression

10:49.277 --> 10:50.511
that they think of you any differently

10:50.545 --> 10:52.212
than Daphne or Toby.

10:52.247 --> 10:53.347
You can't erase history.

10:53.381 --> 10:55.382
I'm the charity case.

10:55.417 --> 10:57.051
The kid that they got stuck with

10:57.085 --> 10:58.919
because my bio mom is a train wreck.

11:00.088 --> 11:02.022
You and your family are in... 

11:02.057 --> 11:03.791
a very unusual situation.

11:03.825 --> 11:07.027
It may feel like they're trying
to vilify your birth mother.

11:07.062 --> 11:09.797
Oh, they're doing it. Trust me.

11:09.831 --> 11:11.732
And it's not just them.

11:11.766 --> 11:13.834
I hear my grandmother say
to my mother all the time

11:13.868 --> 11:15.569
"Remember, Kathryn, she's Puerto Rican.

11:15.604 --> 11:17.404
They're not great at school."

11:17.439 --> 11:20.774
Well, I think you've proven your
grandmother wrong about a hundred times over.

11:20.809 --> 11:23.377
I understand this is important to you,

11:23.411 --> 11:25.613
but I don't think it's
realistic to graduate early.

11:25.647 --> 11:29.049
I think you're gonna have to
sit tight for a while longer.

11:29.084 --> 11:30.184
Yeah.

11:30.218 --> 11:33.120
Uh, okay.

11:33.154 --> 11:34.922
Thank you.

11:40.912 --> 11:41.962
Daphne.

11:43.031 --> 11:45.099
John? Your daughter's here.

11:46.901 --> 11:49.637
I'd like to see what you spent $479 on.

11:50.639 --> 11:51.905
The credit card company called,

11:51.940 --> 11:54.408
warning us of possible fraudulent charges.

11:54.442 --> 11:55.542
- So... 
- At 11:00 A.M.,

11:55.560 --> 11:57.511
which I'm pretty sure
is during school hours.

11:57.545 --> 11:59.380
You guys, I'm so sorry.

11:59.414 --> 12:01.248
I was having a terrible day,

12:01.282 --> 12:02.549
and so Simone and I
decided to go off campus

12:02.584 --> 12:04.485
for just 10 minutes to get smoothies,

12:04.519 --> 12:06.420
and I saw they were having this sale,

12:06.454 --> 12:09.023
so I went in to see if
they had one of those purses

12:09.057 --> 12:09.990
that you wanted... 

12:10.025 --> 12:11.191
No no no no no no no.

12:11.226 --> 12:13.127
You need to know that
there are consequences.

12:13.161 --> 12:15.162
You can forget about going to that party.

12:15.196 --> 12:17.765
What?

12:17.799 --> 12:18.899
Guys... guys, come on.

12:18.933 --> 12:20.668
<i>I said I was sorry.</i>

12:20.702 --> 12:21.935
20 bucks says she gets out of it.

12:21.970 --> 12:23.804
Oh... no way.

12:23.822 --> 12:25.906
Skipping school and charging
up their credit card?

12:25.924 --> 12:27.841
Dad's the weak link. He can't say "no."

12:28.876 --> 12:30.444
He says it to me all the time.

12:30.478 --> 12:33.332
And if he missed out on the
first three years of your life,

12:33.333 --> 12:34.333
maybe he wouldn't.

12:33.748 --> 12:35.749
<i>- It wasn't my fault.
- This is serious, Daphne.</i>

12:35.830 --> 12:38.298
We need to be able to trust you.

12:38.332 --> 12:40.400
I know. I really screwed up.

12:40.434 --> 12:44.204
I am so so so sorry.

12:44.238 --> 12:45.238
We appreciate you coming clean.

12:46.340 --> 12:48.007
She didn't come clean. She got caught.

12:48.042 --> 12:51.878
I just wanted to look cute for the party.

12:51.912 --> 12:54.147
'Cause there's gonna
be so many people there,

12:54.181 --> 12:56.049
and it's hard for me.

12:56.083 --> 12:58.952
I mean, you guys know how
self-conscious I get in crowds.

12:58.986 --> 13:01.621
And trying to keep up
with everybody talking.

13:01.655 --> 13:03.890
She did not just play the cochlear card.

13:03.924 --> 13:06.659
Hey, if you've got an ace, use it.

13:06.694 --> 13:10.530
<i>John: Sweetie, there is no reason
for you to be self-conscious.</i>

13:10.564 --> 13:12.398
You are an amazing young woman.

13:14.368 --> 13:16.603
Okay, this is your one

13:16.637 --> 13:18.238
"get out of jail free" card.

13:18.272 --> 13:19.405
- (Squeals)
- John.

13:19.440 --> 13:21.541
<i>- What?
- She skipped school</i>

13:21.575 --> 13:24.043
to buy a $500 jacket.

13:24.078 --> 13:25.245
Yeah, and she can return the jacket.

13:26.247 --> 13:27.247
So I can go to the party?

13:27.281 --> 13:28.214
Yeah.

13:30.284 --> 13:31.851
(Sighs)

13:31.886 --> 13:33.119
You have to take Bay with you.

13:34.922 --> 13:35.922
(Scoffs)

13:35.956 --> 13:37.991
No way, mom. Come on.

13:38.058 --> 13:39.659
That's the deal.

13:39.693 --> 13:41.795
